caption: Tbh they over hype this restaurant the seafood was decent and the sauce was not my favorite, it was sweet not that hot either, I also got drinks they were not that much $ but it tasted horrible, and the cornbread had jalapenos I asked if they had without them, they said no overall it was okay maybe I have to try one more time.

However they do have large sinks in the middle of the room to wash up. Had the Combo D which feeds two and we had some left over, picture here.  Good atmosphere, friendly staff, Great food! If you are looking for a great spot to enjoy seafood boils, Lowcountry is hard to beat. Unfortunately I wasn't able to dine in, but the place definitely has a following as the wait time was upwards of an hour. My friends and I ordered the Double Double with an extra pound of shrimp which was just enough (we can eat a lot). The spices were the best part. You can dip just about anything in them and it will taste good. The atmosphere was friendly and full of laughter, a welcome sound after such a long lockdown. Overall the food was seasoned well and came out to us piping hot. I would recommend stopping by if you are in the Lake View area.

I ordered for take out, and received notice that my food would be ready around 6:45pm. I arrived at 7:00, was told it would be ready in 20 minutes, and that I would receive a phone call to notify me. 40 minutes later I went back inside to check the status a second time. When I asked how long it would be I was told "I don't know, we'll call you when it's ready." It's now 8:42pm, three hours after I placed my order, and I never received a phone call. I ended up leaving and going home. Absolutely terrible customer service, would not recommend.

There was too much chunky garlic in each bag too, we ended up rinsing some of it off just to eat it. Don’t get me wrong, I love garlic, just not piles of it. Garlic seasoning would be better maybe (or just garlic butter without chopped garlic). The sausage and potatoes inside the bags were delicious! We have so many leftovers too! The jalapeño cornbread was tasty also. I don’t like spicy foods and this was just spicy enough to taste good.

First time to the restaurant and the food is phenomenal but the service is lacking on training. A group of us attended there for a birthday celebration and was greeted and seated right away. After buying food and drinks and being seated for almost an hour and a half the manager walks up to us to tell us we have to leave because we had too many in our party and had to split tables. No one besides the initial group was there. The way JONATHAN, the manager, came to us was highly disrespectful and not how it should of been handled. Another thing we noticed was that there was nothing but African American men and women there when we got in. When we left, the crowd was totally different and no one if any type of color was there. From any way I look at it it just screams of racial intent. It changed from us having a good time to everyone looking at us because we had a problem with how we were addressed. We kept it classy and professional but will never go back here and I hope you don’t either. Support who supports us!!

I really do love lowcountry but I have to say I wish the consistency of the garlic sauce would be the same everytime.  Ive been here four times and there are two times where it was way too salty.  Seafood is already salty so it doesn't need a lot more.  I also asked for less salt.  There were pockets of salt that I just stayed away from plus it didn't have as much garlic in it as before.   There use to be a classic sauce one of the servers suggested to me.   I did half garlic  and half classic which was perfect....best meal I had here.  I also have to say, not crazy about the new service style.  Ok, you order your own food,  someone brings it to you.   During the time I was there, no one came to see how the food was or to pick up the finished trays or full bucket that we were jamming shells into.  I go to order dessert, the person brings it over and really doesn't have a clear spot to place it.  Why didn't you take some garbage away?   I would like to eat my dessert without swiping garlic sauce or seafood juices.  I  just think the enjoyable touches of dining service here are gone.

I didnt like the fact that if you order a drink, its in a can. So no refills. My wife loved the corn bread and I had the rice. The beignets were delicious also, but I was not a fan of the nutella ones. The nutella was watery and even though it was inside the beignet, i think it would have tasted better if it was a thicker sauce, maybe even a spread. I just visited New Orleans and the sugar ones were similar, but it needed a lot more powdered sugar to compare to Cafe Du Monde. I will be returning for sure.

Being a seafood lover I was excited to try low country.  Food- You can select a variety of seafood to combine with seasoning and a spice level. We went with crab and shrimp paired with hot everything seasoning (garlic, lemon pepper, Cajun) and one Cajun only. The seafood was good but included too much seasoning that took away the natural flavor of the seafood. In addition we ordered corn, potatoes and cornbread which were standard.  Service- We were in and out in less than an hour due to having other plans. They do offer a hand washing station to clean up after which is nice.  Overall decent choice if in the area, but if I return I would ask for lighter seasoning or possibly opt for just one.

Where to start? This place has evolved since it first opened a few years back, but has stayed true to its core mission--shellfish boiled in butter and spices.  They offer the traditional mussels, clams, shrimp, crab and lobster.  In addition, they have recently added gumbo, and a bunch of extra sides like cajun fries, mac n cheese, and chicken biscuit sandwiches.  They have a full bar that includes house-mixed specialty cocktails, many of them unique, like spicy mandarin orange Margueritas and house infused highballs.  They have a really good happy hour from 5-7 including food specials as well as half price drinks if you order food at the bar.  Family friendly and low-key, this is an easy place to come and have a fun, relaxing meal.

I went to this little hidden-ish gem with my boyfriend and his parents a little bit ago. When they visit, we like to take them to interesting spots and this one did not disappoint. Don't ask me why, but I just felt so official with that damn bib and I was ready to eat and make us of it, like nobody's business. Besides the seafood, the corn was my favorite item. I guess there is nothing that special about it but for me it was just cooked perfectly and that is pure bliss (what can I say, I am an easy gal to please).  PROS: - Excellent seafood in a bag, in Chicago - There is a hand washing sink in the middle of the restaurant - The food tasted fresh - Service was great  CONS: - Messy eating (but we knew what we signed-up for!) - Major con: Be ready to expel some pretty FOUL smelling gas  All in all we had a wonderful time and I cannot wait to return!!
